Measuring and Monitoring Data Integrity
You can't improve what you don't measure. Establish key metrics to monitor your data integrity:

Database Accuracy Rate: What percentage of your database records have been recently validated and verified? Track this monthly. Your goal should be maintaining 95%+ accuracy in critical fields like email address, job title, and company name.

Email Deliverability Rate: Monitor bounce rates, unsubscribe rates, and complaint rates. These metrics reflect data quality issues. A decline in deliverability often signals underlying data integrity problems.

Duplicate Record Rate: How many duplicate records are in your database? Track this metric and watch for increases. Growing duplicate rates indicate problems in your data intake processes.

Data Age: When was each record last updated? Reports should show what percentage of your database was updated within the last 90 days, 180 days, or 360 days. More recent updates indicate better data freshness.

